[DhtmlXQ_comment4]For beginners,||although red plays his right cannon as the central cannon and black plays his right elephant, ECCO deems this as the left central cannon variation for red, and the left elephant variation for black. This is because, ECCO deems P3+1 as the opening move for the Angel's pawn opening by default.||A slight flaw in the system... LOL.[/DhtmlXQ_comment4]
[DhtmlXQ_comment13]At this stage in the game, the development of red's chess pieces are faster but black has the cross river pawn. ||It would be relatively even at this stage for both sides.[/DhtmlXQ_comment13]
[DhtmlXQ_comment17]This is a less played variation for red!||E7+5 is the more commonly played move. ||Another game with a similar opening was played in the same year, whereby Heilongjiang Province's Master Nie Tiewen lost to Guangdong Province's Zhang Xuechao.[/DhtmlXQ_comment17]
